            <h2>Research & Academic Leadership</h2>
            <p>He is a Professor of Fetal Medicine at the University of Oxford, leading research in fetal growth restriction, Doppler ultrasound markers, and third-trimester scans. His work guides both clinical practice and future innovation.</p>
            <img src="https://www.ouh.nhs.uk/media/hasdnmvf/lawrence-impey.jpg" alt="Research Work">
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Guideline & Policy Impact</h2>
            <p>Lawrence has chaired RCOG guidelines on breech presentation and other maternal-fetal conditions, standardizing care across the UK and improving outcomes for thousands of mothers and babies.</p>
            <img src="https://www.abebooks.com/9780198838678/Oxford-Handbook-Obstetrics-Gynaecology-Medical-0198838670/plp?utm_source=chatgpt.com" alt="Guidelines and Textbooks">
